= Action name = PCK.AUTOMIC_YAML.PUB.ACTION.GET_YAML_CONTENT
= General description = This Action will retrieve YAML content from specified YAML path.
= Inputs = * YAML File Path : Provide full path to the YAML file.. E.g. D:\Content_filePath.txt * YAML Content : Provide YAML content or an AE variable that contains YAML content. E.g. &YAML# * Path to YAML Element* : Provide valid path to the YAML element to retrieve its value. E.g.: $.Dev.Server * Fail if path does not exist : Specify whether the action should fail, if path does not exist. Default: YES
Note: YAML File Path and YAML Content are mutually exclusive.
= Failure Conditions = * If the user provides invalid YAML file path location or invalid YAML Content. * If 'Fail if path does not exist' field is selected as YES and specified Path to YAML Element does not exist.
= Behavior = (none)
=Return Value= UC4RB_YAML_DATA# : YAML Path Value UC4RB_YAML_VALUE_EXISTS# : Flag to check if value exists. false if value is null.
= Outputs = * Return code is 0 in case of success. * Return code is non-zero in case of failure.
= Rollback = (none)
= Logging = AE logs will be displayed in the AE report.
= Example = * YAML File Path : C:\yaml.txt * YAML Content : * Path to YAML Element : $.Dev.Server.IP * Fail if path does not exist : YES --------------------------------------------- * YAML File Path : * YAML Content : - martin: name: Martin D'vloper job: Developer * Path to YAML Element : $.martin.name * Fail if path does not exist : NO
